  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I remove adware and spyware virus?",
  "response": "Removing adware and spyware from your computer can help enhance your privacy and improve system performance. Here are the steps you can follow to ensure a thorough removal:\n\n### 1. Backup Your Data\nBefore proceeding, it\u2019s a good idea to back up important data to prevent loss during the cleaning process.\n\n### 2. Disconnect from the Internet\nTo minimize any further damage and prevent the adware from sending data or further installing additional unwanted software, disconnect your computer from the internet.\n\n### 3. Use Built-in Security Tools\n- **Windows Defender (Windows 10/11)**: Run a full scan via Windows Defender.\n  1. Open **Settings** > **Update & Security** > **Windows Security**.\n  2. Click on **Virus & threat protection**.\n  3. Click on **Scan options** and select **Full scan**.\n  4. Follow the prompts.\n\n### 4. Remove Unwanted Programs\n1. **Windows**:\n   - Open **Control Panel** > **Programs** > **Programs and Features**.\n   - Look for unfamiliar programs that may be associated with adware or spyware, select them, and click **Uninstall**.\n\n2. **Mac**:\n   - Go to **Applications** and look for suspicious applications. Drag them to the Trash and empty it.\n\n### 5. Use Anti-Malware Software\nConsider using reputable anti-malware software to scan and remove adware and spyware. Some popular options include:\n- **Malwarebytes**: Download and install, then run a full scan to detect and remove threats.\n- **AdwCleaner**: A free tool specifically designed to find and remove adware.\n  \n### 6. Reset Your Web Browser\nAdware often changes browser settings. Resetting your browser can help:\n- **Chrome**: Settings > Advanced > Reset and clean up > Restore settings to their original defaults.\n- **Firefox**: Help > Troubleshooting Information > Refresh Firefox.\n- **Edge**: Settings > Reset settings > Restore settings to their default values.\n\n### 7. Clear Browser Cache and Data\nClear your browser cache and cookies to remove any remnants of adware:\n- Go to your browser\u2019s settings and look for the option to clear browsing data/history.\n\n### 8. Check Browser Extensions\nReview and disable/remove unnecessary or suspicious extensions/add-ons in your web browsers.\n\n### 9. Enable Firewall Protection\nEnsure that your firewall is enabled to provide an additional layer of security. You can do this through:\n- **Windows Defender Firewall** on Windows.\n- **System Preferences** > **Security & Privacy** on Mac to check your firewall settings.\n\n### 10. Keep Your Software Updated\nRegularly update your operating system and all software to protect against vulnerabilities that adware and spyware can exploit.\n\n### 11. Educate Yourself on Safe Browsing Practices\nTo help prevent future infections, be cautious about downloading files and clicking links from untrusted sources. Always opt for custom installation settings and avoid clicking on ads or pop-ups that seem suspicious.\n\nIf the adware or spyware persists after following these steps, you may want to consider seeking help from a professional technician.",
